he ages, so the critical examination of the issues involved sheds intriguing light on the cultural history from late antiquity to the seventeenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEuropean literatureyRenaissance, 1450-1600xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aOld age in literature. 0aOld agezEuropexHistory. 4aAlter /i. d. Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aEarly Modern Age.  aLate Antiquity.  aLiterature, History, and Art History.  aMiddle Ages.  aOld Age Studies.1 aBerthelot, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBostock, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCoudert, Allison P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarver, Valerie L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanssen, Anouk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJost, Jean Ε., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLazda-Cazers, Rasma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyon, Jonathan R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMieszkowski, Gretchen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeacock, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPigg, Daniel F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1